<HEADLINE>
<P>
FEINSTEIN, WILSON CAMPAIGNS FOR GOVERNOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The debate over who did what in the S&amp;L debacle is a subordinate issue in 
the contest for California's governorship. 
</P>
<P>
My concern is "Republicanism." 
</P>
<P>
Years of promoting and provoking anti-women, anti-minority, anti-civil rights 
and liberties, anti-peace, anti-self-determinism, anti-consumer legislation, 
policies and attitudes in Washington and Sacramento have solidified my 
determination to avoid any candidate, local or national, who choses to label 
him/herself Republican. 
</P>
<P>
LOUIS ST. MARTIN 
</P>
<P>
Pomona 
</P>
</TEXT>
