<P>
TROJANS SEND MESSAGE BY REINSTATING PLAYERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The news of the assault on a woman graduate student at USC was indeed shocking 
to me. 
</P>
<P>
However, I was outraged when I read that the students (allegedly) involved 
continue to practice with the football team. 
</P>
<P>
I am well aware that the legal aspects of this case have yet to be resolved. It 
seems to me that the issue here is not one of legality but of morality. 
</P>
<P>
The message sent by allowing these students continued participation in the USC 
athletic program is clear: violence and sexual abuse of women is permitted at 
USC. 
</P>
<P>
SISTER JO ANN DeQUATTRO 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
