175, Sr.; Hieu Nguyen, RB/DB, 5-7, 155, Jr. 
</P>
<P>
Outlook: The Rebels were league co-champions with Valencia last season, but had 
to forfeit the title because of an ineligible player. "I think the kids have 
been very positive about what happened," DiPalma said. "And they are very 
determined." Whether that will mean continued success depends on how well the 
Rebels fill the holes. Landry, a starting defensive back last season, has the 
toughest assignment as he moves to running back to replace Kenison PoChing (900 
yards). The secondary is sound with Hien and Hoan Nguyen, who are brothers, and 
Hieu Nguyen, who is not related. 
</P>
<P>
Western 
</P>
<P>
